Anomalies of the (a) ocean heat content (1022 J) (ocean impact), (b) vertical wind shear (m s−1) (dynamical impact), and (c) potential intensity (m s−1) (thermodynamical impact) over the eastern Main Development Region by total (A), linear trend (B), detrended (C), ENSO impact, AMM impact, and the NAO impact in August/September 2017. Note that detrending was done for the data available period 1982–2017.

In order to examine how much of the detrended anomaly in 2017 is explained by a combination of ENSO, the AMM, and the NAO modes, the anomaly is projected onto the REOFs of each mode. For example, the reconstructed SSTENSO (x, y, t) for the ENSO mode at (x, y) and time t is then2\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
